title: Country Music | Fox News
description: Dive into the world of country music with the latest news and updates surrounding stars like Morgan Wallen, Lainey Wilson, Jelly Roll and more. Discover country music's evolution from its southern roots to modern hits with Fox News Digital.

Answer: Country music is a musical genre originating from rural parts of the southern regions across the U.S. It is famous in cities like Nashville, Memphis, Austin, and other major cities in the United States.
Country music can often be identified with traditional sounds from banjos, fiddles, harmonicas and guitars. Lyrics often include storytelling elements about heartbreaks, love, loss and good times.

Answer: Johnny Cash and June Carter, Merle Haggard, Patsy Cline, Hank Williams Jr., The Judds, Waylon Jennings, Loretta Lynn, and Kenny Rogers are among some of the most influential artists who helped shape country music.
"I Walk the Line" by Cash and "Walkin' After Midnight" by Cline are among the greatest country hits from the 1950s and 1960s.
Country rock artists like Jimmy Buffett, the Allman Brothers Band, and the Marshall Tucker Band provided audiences of the genre with a unique perspective on the sound.

"Coal Miner's Daughter" by Loretta Lynn, "I've Always Been Crazy" by Waylon Jennings, "Margaritaville" by Buffett, and "Ramblin' Man" by the Allman Brothers are a few of the most recognizable country songs from the 1970s.

In the 1980s, country music artists like George Strait, Alan Jackson, Reba McEntire, Willie Nelson, Dolly Parton, and Randy Travis became widely recognized before skyrocketing to fame and maintaining popularity today.
Brooks & Dunn, Garth Brooks, Kenny Chesney, Tim McGraw, Toby Keith, Shania Twain, and Trisha Yearwood paved the way for pop-like country music in the 1990s.
In the early 2000s, some of the most popular artists included Keith Urban, Toby Keith, Faith Hill, Carrie Underwood, The Chicks and Kenny Chesney, among others.

In the 2010s, Eric Church, Miranda Lambert, Blake Shelton, Jason Aldean, Kacey Musgraves, Thomas Rhett, Sam Hunt, Brantley Gilbert, Luke Combs and Chris Stapleton were among the most popular country artists.

Answer: Since 2000, country music has seen a multitude of artists emerge as top performers and top-charting singers and songwriters, including Jason Aldean, Kelsea Ballerini, Dierks Bentley, Kane Brown, Zac Brown Band, Luke Bryan, Kenny Chesney, Eric Church, The Chicks, Luke Combs, Sheryl Crow, Billy Currington, Russell Dickerson, Old Dominion, Rascal Flatts, Brantley Gilbert, Faith Hill, Sam Hunt, Cody Johnson, Toby Keith, Miranda Lambert, Megan Moroney, Martina McBride, Tim McGraw, Kacey Musgraves, Brad Paisley, Jelly Roll, Darius Rucker, Thomas Rhett, Lee Brice, Blake Shelton, Chris Stapleton, Carrie Underwood, Keith Urban, Morgan Wallen and Lainey Wilson.
Answer: The Country Music Association Awards is the award ceremony that recognizes country music artists for their achievements.
Each year, people vote on their country artist nominees to win in different categories. This ceremony is also known as the  CMA Awards or CMAs.

In 2024, Morgan Wallen won entertainer of the year. "White Horse" by Chris Stapleton won single of the year and "Leather" by Cody Johnson won album of the year. Lainey Wilson succeeded as female vocalist of the year and Megan Moroney emerged as new artist of the year.
